---
layout: layouts/_base.njk
title: Projects
headerText: PROJECTS & POLICY PROPOSALS
introductionBlurb: |
  Our current program of work is focused around four themes which convey our commitment to shaping positive, pluralistic possible futures in partnership with communities all around the world. We welcome new ideas and invite you to co-design the next experiment for your community.

  - **Democratic  Transformation** - Forging the foundations of 21st century governance

  - **Resilient Decentralization** - Accelerating local creativity and distributed participation to solve global problems

  - **Collective Agency** - Empowering "plural publics" to form and act in the face of new shared challenges

  - **Imaginative Hope** - Inspiring curiosity, experimentation and agency to shape possible futures
projectsBlurb: |
  Since 2018, RxC has applied our methods, tools and research in collaboration with communities around the world, from state and local government to creative practice, in web3 communities and with policymakers: we have found every kind of governance system and community can benefit from new tools for participation, collaboration, resource-management and consensus-building. 

  To support the translation of experiments, research and edge practice into the mainstream policy reform agenda, and to inspire elected representatives, creative bureaucrats, advocates and cultural innovators, RxC also develops policy frameworks, proposals and submissions on a range of topics across civic tech, digital rights and democratic participation. 

  Review and download case studies of our past projects, or explore our projects, proposals and impacts through a timeline of our work to date.
proposalsBlurb: |
